<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1339,1940]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1700,1724]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name derives from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[725,798,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">hyalus</emphasis>
= glass and 
<emphasis box="[931,999,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">penna</emphasis>
= wing”, alluding to transparent wings, although this species is no more clear-winged than many others.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
